The father of Nasarawa Governor, Abdullahi Sule, Alhaji Sule Bawa, has been rushed to Dalhart Arab Speacilist Hospital (DASH) in Lafia. Bawa is Emir of Gudi Town n Akwanga Local Government Area of Nasarawa State. A resident of Gudi who prefers anonymity said: “The Chief of Gudi, Alhaji Sule Bawa developed fever and started coughing. “This led for his rush to the VIP section of Dalhatu Araf Specialist Hospital, (DASH) in Lafia on Wednesday. “Same Wednesday, a team of health personnel fumigated the Palace and the Personal residence of the Governor.” When contacted, the Chief Medical Director of DASH, Dr Hassan Ikrimat, simply said: ” It is unethical to disclose the identity of any patient.” 